abstract: Nineteen-year-old Norbu Damdrul becomes eighth Tibetan monk or former monk to set himself on fire to protest Chinese rule.
snippet: Norbu Damdrul, 19, was the eighth Tibetan monk or former monk to set himself on fire to protest China since March. He survived.
lead_paragraph: Norbu Damdrul, 19, was the eighth Tibetan monk or former monk to set himself on fire to protest China since March. He survived.

headline.main: Another Tibetan Sets Fire to Self Over China Rule
